WEBVTT

00:00.500 --> 00:04.042
♪♪

00:08.709 --> 00:09.814
Are you sure this

00:09.815 --> 00:10.918
isn't too mean?

00:10.959 --> 00:12.042
No!

00:12.083 --> 00:13.351
- Haven't you ever
- heard the saying,

00:13.375 --> 00:14.438
"The ends justify

00:14.439 --> 00:15.500
the mean"?

00:16.584 --> 00:18.125
- Oh, yeah.
- All right, let's go.

00:21.626 --> 00:23.250
(CELL PHONE CHIMING)

00:24.375 --> 00:25.459
(GRUNTING)

00:27.083 --> 00:28.500
(CHUCKLES)

00:31.334 --> 00:34.876
Hmm, blocked number.

00:34.918 --> 00:36.043
Oh, well.

00:36.044 --> 00:37.167
Live on the edge,

00:34.918 --> 00:37.167
Bertram!

00:38.083 --> 00:39.375
(CHUCKLES) Hello?

00:39.417 --> 00:41.059
- (WITH NEW YORK ACCENT)
- Hello, is this Bertram Winkle?

00:41.083 --> 00:42.083
Speaking.

00:44.000 --> 00:45.750
I'm calling from Manhattan's

00:45.751 --> 00:47.500
number one opera

00:44.000 --> 00:47.500
station, WOPR.

00:47.542 --> 00:49.042
Really?

00:49.043 --> 00:50.542
I love Whopper!

00:50.584 --> 00:52.314
Thanks to your

00:52.315 --> 00:54.042
faithful listenership

00:50.584 --> 00:54.042
and many,

00:54.083 --> 00:55.772
many emails on how

00:55.773 --> 00:57.459
to improve our playlist,

00:57.500 --> 00:59.272
you have won dinner

00:59.273 --> 01:01.042
for two at Le Bon Repas!

01:01.083 --> 01:02.355
(GASPS) Oh, my gosh!

01:02.356 --> 01:03.626
Dinner for two!

01:03.667 --> 01:04.855
Wait. Do I have

01:04.855 --> 01:06.042
to bring someone,

01:06.083 --> 01:07.563
or can I just eat

01:07.564 --> 01:09.042
the two meals myself?

01:09.083 --> 01:10.105
Uh, that's between

01:10.106 --> 01:11.125
you and the management.

01:12.626 --> 01:14.042
But there's more!

01:14.083 --> 01:15.918
Ooh, dinner for three?

01:15.959 --> 01:16.959
No, geez!

01:18.167 --> 01:19.605
The "more" is that

01:19.606 --> 01:21.042
celebrity chef

01:18.167 --> 01:21.042
Anthony Monsanto

01:21.083 --> 01:22.813
will personally serve you

01:22.814 --> 01:24.542
his famous 12-course

01:21.083 --> 01:24.542
tasting menu.

01:24.584 --> 01:25.834
- And to give you
- a preview,

01:25.876 --> 01:27.272
He's sending over

01:27.273 --> 01:28.667
the first course right now!

01:28.709 --> 01:29.834
(EXCLAIMS GLEEFULLY)

01:29.835 --> 01:30.959
(ELEVATOR BELL DINGS)

01:32.709 --> 01:34.292
- What took you so long?
- (CHUCKLES)

01:36.584 --> 01:37.792
Bon appetit, sucker!

01:37.793 --> 01:39.000
(EXCLAIMS)

01:39.042 --> 01:40.167
(ALL LAUGHING)

01:41.083 --> 01:43.000
You just got served!

01:44.250 --> 01:45.459
That's it!

01:45.500 --> 01:47.272
I am done dealing

01:47.273 --> 01:49.042
with you horrible kids.

01:49.083 --> 01:50.563
Plus, I am sick and

01:50.564 --> 01:52.042
tired of being treated

01:49.083 --> 01:52.042
like a servant!

01:52.083 --> 01:53.042
You are a servant.

01:53.083 --> 01:54.105
Not anymore.

01:54.106 --> 01:55.125
I quit!

01:55.167 --> 01:57.000
(EMMA GASPS)

01:57.042 --> 01:58.125
That's the last time

01:58.167 --> 01:59.807
- we pretend to give
- him something nice.

02:01.292 --> 02:02.855
I have to pack my things

02:02.856 --> 02:04.417
first, but after that I quit!

02:06.584 --> 02:08.126
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh

02:08.127 --> 02:09.667
Oh, oh, oh, oh

02:09.709 --> 02:13.209
♪ Hey Jessie, hey Jessie

02:13.250 --> 02:14.939
♪ It feels like a party

02:14.940 --> 02:16.626
every day

02:16.667 --> 02:20.334
♪ Hey Jessie, hey Jessie

02:20.375 --> 02:22.209
♪ But they keep on pulling

02:22.210 --> 02:24.042
me every which way

02:24.083 --> 02:27.500
♪ Hey Jessie, hey Jessie

02:27.542 --> 02:29.313
♪ My whole world is changing

02:29.314 --> 02:31.083
Turning around

02:31.125 --> 02:33.084
♪ They got me going crazy

02:33.085 --> 02:35.042
Yeah, they're shaking

02:31.125 --> 02:35.042
the ground

02:35.083 --> 02:36.647
♪ But they took a chance

02:36.648 --> 02:38.209
on the new girl in town

02:38.250 --> 02:40.147
♪ And I don't want to let them

02:40.148 --> 02:42.042
down, down, down

02:42.083 --> 02:43.083
♪ Hey Jessie

02:45.459 --> 02:47.167
♪ Hey Jessie

02:49.125 --> 02:50.876
♪ It feels like a party

02:50.877 --> 02:52.626
every day

02:52.667 --> 02:54.334
♪ Hey, hey, hey,

02:54.335 --> 02:56.000
hey, hey, Jessie ♪

03:00.209 --> 03:01.268
Thanks for helping me study

03:01.292 --> 03:03.042
- for my foreign language
- mid-term.

03:03.083 --> 03:04.310
- I didn't know
- you spoke German.

03:04.334 --> 03:05.751
Oh, I do not.

03:05.792 --> 03:07.667
- But your college
- is not accredited,

03:07.709 --> 03:09.417
- So how hard can
- this test be?

03:10.083 --> 03:11.334
Fair enough.

03:11.375 --> 03:12.709
They actually offer

03:12.710 --> 03:14.042
Conversational Pig Latin.

03:14.083 --> 03:15.751
- Jessie, something
- horrible happened!

03:15.792 --> 03:17.209
- Whoa, whoa,
- whoa! Okay.

03:17.250 --> 03:18.626
- It's not
- that horrible.

03:18.667 --> 03:19.897
Uh, it's not like that time

03:19.898 --> 03:21.125
we lost Ravi camping.

03:21.167 --> 03:22.271
That was a very

03:22.272 --> 03:23.375
uncomfortable night.

03:23.417 --> 03:24.751
- Raccoons are
- not as cuddly

03:24.792 --> 03:26.626
- Or chatty as they
- appear in cartoons.

03:28.500 --> 03:30.459
- Luke's right.
- It's not a big deal.

03:30.500 --> 03:31.542
Mmm-mmm.

03:31.584 --> 03:32.542
Uh-uh-uh.

03:32.584 --> 03:33.647
Less walking.

03:33.648 --> 03:34.709
More talking.

03:34.751 --> 03:35.897
Bertram quit. See?

03:35.898 --> 03:37.042
No biggie. (CHUCKLES)

03:37.083 --> 03:38.042
What?

03:38.083 --> 03:39.709
No it is a big biggie!

03:39.751 --> 03:41.042
Why did he quit?

03:41.083 --> 03:42.375
Well, we sorta kinda...

03:42.417 --> 03:43.643
- (MUFFLED PROTESTS)
- No idea, really.

03:43.667 --> 03:45.083
He's just weird.

03:49.667 --> 03:51.167
Wow!

03:51.209 --> 03:52.813
I still can't believe

03:52.814 --> 03:54.417
Bertram actually quit.

03:54.459 --> 03:56.167
- Guys, relax.
- He'll be back.

03:56.209 --> 03:57.834
- He could never
- get another job.

03:57.876 --> 03:59.042
Guess what?

03:59.083 --> 04:00.417
I got another job!

04:00.459 --> 04:01.834
(BERTRAM CHUCKLES)

04:01.876 --> 04:03.252
Just here to grab

04:03.253 --> 04:04.626
Polly the pitcher.

04:04.667 --> 04:06.126
Who would be desperate

04:06.127 --> 04:07.584
enough to hire Bertram?

04:07.626 --> 04:09.250
Hello, urchins.

04:09.292 --> 04:10.292
Urchin Keeper.

04:11.709 --> 04:13.042
- Have you heard
- the news?

04:13.083 --> 04:14.292
I've got myself a new

04:14.293 --> 04:15.500
heaping hunk o' help.

04:17.416 --> 04:18.522
Hi, boss.

04:18.523 --> 04:19.625
Hi, Bertie.

04:17.416 --> 04:19.625
(GIGGLES)

04:20.709 --> 04:22.000
See you

04:22.002 --> 04:23.292
around, urchins!

04:26.125 --> 04:27.396
Bertram working for

04:27.397 --> 04:28.667
Mrs. Chesterfield?

04:28.709 --> 04:30.500
- This is like
- a bad dream.

04:30.542 --> 04:31.626
Somebody pinch me.

04:31.667 --> 04:33.542
- I'm on it.
- Somebody else.

04:40.083 --> 04:41.397
I guess Bertram

04:41.398 --> 04:42.709
is not coming

04:40.083 --> 04:42.709
back after all.

04:42.751 --> 04:45.043
So, who's gonna occasionally

04:45.044 --> 04:47.334
clean stuff and

04:42.751 --> 04:47.334
defrost meals for us?

04:48.459 --> 04:49.626
Guys, do we even

04:49.627 --> 04:50.792
really need a butler?

04:50.834 --> 04:52.667
- We could just clean up
- after ourselves.

04:52.709 --> 04:54.667
- Yeah! How hard
- can it be?

04:56.792 --> 04:58.834
Okay!

04:59.500 --> 05:01.042
How did this happen?

05:01.083 --> 05:02.480
It has only been an hour

05:02.481 --> 05:03.876
and we never left the couch.

05:05.626 --> 05:06.689
Maybe Bertram really

05:06.690 --> 05:07.751
did do stuff.

05:07.792 --> 05:09.751
- Yeah, you know
- what he did?

05:09.792 --> 05:11.042
He walked out on us!

05:11.083 --> 05:12.292
To work for the enemy!

05:12.334 --> 05:14.209
- How could he just
- leave us like that?

05:14.250 --> 05:15.292
Right?

05:15.334 --> 05:17.042
- I mean, sure,
- we were rude,

05:17.083 --> 05:18.563
And messy, and took

05:18.564 --> 05:20.042
him for granted,

05:20.083 --> 05:21.459
but we are so

05:21.460 --> 05:22.834
gosh darn cute!

05:24.667 --> 05:26.584
Hey, where's Zuri?

05:26.626 --> 05:28.042
ZURI: I'm under here!

05:28.959 --> 05:30.085
And we need

05:30.086 --> 05:31.209
a new butler, stat!

05:37.250 --> 05:39.042
- Good morning,
- Mrs. Chesterfield.

05:39.083 --> 05:40.418
Please, Bertie,

05:40.419 --> 05:41.751
call me Rhoda.

05:41.792 --> 05:43.856
Okay. But remember,

05:43.857 --> 05:45.918
you promised we'd keep

05:41.792 --> 05:45.918
things professional.

05:45.959 --> 05:47.105
I'll let you know

05:47.106 --> 05:48.250
if you cross a line.

05:50.334 --> 05:51.334
So, what would you

05:51.335 --> 05:52.335
like for breakfast?

05:52.375 --> 05:54.209
Bertie, don't worry

05:54.210 --> 05:56.042
your handsome little

05:52.375 --> 05:56.042
head about cooking.

05:56.083 --> 05:57.626
- (CHUCKLES)
- (YELLS) Martha!

06:00.083 --> 06:01.083
Oh, thank you!

06:01.084 --> 06:02.084
Mmm-hmm.

06:02.125 --> 06:03.209
But if you have a maid,

06:03.210 --> 06:04.292
why do you need a butler?

06:04.334 --> 06:06.001
Oh, I do like to have

06:06.002 --> 06:07.667
a lot of help on hand.

06:07.709 --> 06:09.083
- And a lot of hands
- on the help.

06:09.125 --> 06:10.459
(GIGGLES)

06:12.918 --> 06:14.292
But, I...

06:14.334 --> 06:16.001
Bertie, Bertie,

06:16.002 --> 06:17.667
you're working

06:14.334 --> 06:17.667
for Rhoda now!

06:17.709 --> 06:18.751
(CHUCKLES)

06:18.792 --> 06:20.709
Why not take a nap?

06:20.751 --> 06:22.417
- I know you're
- a nap man.

06:22.459 --> 06:23.730
Well, I have been up

06:23.731 --> 06:25.000
for an hour already.

06:25.042 --> 06:26.751
- Uh-huh.
- (CHUCKLES)

06:26.792 --> 06:28.772
Oh, I was so glad

06:28.773 --> 06:30.751
I could rescue you

06:26.792 --> 06:30.751
from those

06:30.792 --> 06:32.230
rotten ragamuffins and

06:32.231 --> 06:33.667
their noxious nanny.

06:33.709 --> 06:35.209
- They were
- so mean to me.

06:35.250 --> 06:36.751
Yeah.

06:36.792 --> 06:38.376
Yes, yes, the mean

06:38.377 --> 06:39.959
children are awful.

06:40.000 --> 06:42.042
But you're here now,

06:42.083 --> 06:43.626
- loved and
- appreciated.

06:43.667 --> 06:44.792
(SIGHS)

06:44.834 --> 06:46.751
- This is the best - job ever.
- (CHUCKLES)

06:48.751 --> 06:50.292
- MRS. CHESTERFIELD:
- Martha, hush!

06:50.334 --> 06:51.376
Must you walk

06:51.377 --> 06:52.417
like a truck driver?

06:54.250 --> 06:55.751
So hard to find good help.

06:55.792 --> 06:57.709
- Yes! Yes!
- (SIGHS)

07:01.959 --> 07:03.667
He's the best one yet.

07:03.709 --> 07:05.209
- Yeah, you've got
- to be impressed

07:05.250 --> 07:06.293
With a guy who

07:06.294 --> 07:07.334
served appetizers

07:05.250 --> 07:07.334
on the Mayflower.

07:10.792 --> 07:11.834
Hello.

07:11.876 --> 07:13.542
I am Roger Bevans,

07:13.584 --> 07:14.709
and I am here

07:14.710 --> 07:15.834
to apply for

07:13.584 --> 07:15.834
the butler position.

07:15.876 --> 07:17.626
Gods be praised!

07:17.667 --> 07:19.647
He is neat and has

07:19.648 --> 07:21.626
already eschewed the use

07:17.667 --> 07:21.626
of two contractions.

07:21.667 --> 07:23.000
(CROAKING)

07:23.751 --> 07:26.417
Oh, an Asian water monitor,

07:26.459 --> 07:28.250
- the noblest
- of all the lizards.

07:28.292 --> 07:29.918
- Bertram, who?
- (CHUCKLES)

07:30.918 --> 07:32.542
- Hi, I'm Jessie.
- I'm the nanny.

07:32.584 --> 07:34.209
- And this is
- the Ross Family.

07:34.250 --> 07:36.042
How do you do?

07:36.083 --> 07:37.042
- Uh, why don't you - tell us a little bit
- About yourself?

07:37.083 --> 07:38.667
Certainly.

07:38.709 --> 07:39.751
I have a degree in

07:39.752 --> 07:40.792
home economics

07:38.709 --> 07:40.792
and food science

07:40.834 --> 07:42.709
from the Sorbonne.

07:42.751 --> 07:44.022
And I've worked for some

07:44.023 --> 07:45.292
of the finest households

07:42.751 --> 07:45.292
in three continents.

07:45.334 --> 07:46.792
Wow!

07:46.834 --> 07:48.209
That's every continent!

07:50.209 --> 07:52.417
So, Mr. Fancy Britches,

07:52.459 --> 07:53.727
- why do you want
- to work here?

07:53.751 --> 07:55.375
Zuri!

07:55.417 --> 07:57.105
(CLEARS THROAT)

07:57.106 --> 07:58.792
That is a good question,

07:55.417 --> 07:58.792
Mr. Fancy Britches.

07:58.834 --> 08:00.418
Let's just say,

08:00.419 --> 08:02.000
I enjoy a challenge.

08:02.042 --> 08:04.000
- Perfect!
- I'm a challenge.

08:05.334 --> 08:06.667
Yeah, he's not kidding.

08:06.709 --> 08:08.789
- His room is so dirty,
- the cockroaches complained.

08:09.751 --> 08:10.918
You're hired. (CHUCKLES)

08:12.667 --> 08:13.751
(BERTRAM HUMMING)

08:15.792 --> 08:17.856
Bertie, I brought

08:17.857 --> 08:19.918
you something sweet

08:15.792 --> 08:19.918
to nibble on.

08:19.959 --> 08:21.000
And some grapes.

08:22.751 --> 08:24.500
Uh-uh-uh!

08:24.542 --> 08:25.792
Allow me.

08:29.083 --> 08:30.542
I feel a little

08:30.543 --> 08:32.000
uncomfortable with this.

08:32.042 --> 08:33.270
Well then let's

08:33.272 --> 08:34.500
get a little

08:32.042 --> 08:34.500
more comfortable.

08:34.542 --> 08:35.876
(CHUCKLES)

08:35.918 --> 08:37.208
Is it getting hot

08:37.210 --> 08:38.500
in here?

08:35.918 --> 08:38.500
(GASPS)

08:38.542 --> 08:39.667
You feel it too?

08:39.668 --> 08:40.792
(CHUCKLES)

08:40.833 --> 08:43.583
Oh! Isn't this fun?

08:43.626 --> 08:44.709
Bertie, I bought

08:44.710 --> 08:45.792
you a present.

08:45.834 --> 08:47.000
- You did?
- Mmm-hmm.

08:50.083 --> 08:51.459
It's your

08:51.460 --> 08:52.834
new uniform.

08:52.876 --> 08:54.375
Where's the rest of it?

08:54.417 --> 08:56.059
- Wait till you see - what I make you
- Wear in the summer.

08:56.083 --> 08:58.042
(CHUCKLING)

08:58.083 --> 09:00.042
Now go put it on.

09:00.083 --> 09:01.355
Oh, look! Uh, your

09:01.356 --> 09:02.626
tulips need attention.

09:02.667 --> 09:04.417
- I thought
- you'd never notice.

09:05.918 --> 09:07.000
(MAKES KISSING NOISES)

09:07.042 --> 09:08.542
(EXCLAIMING)

09:13.042 --> 09:14.709
Breakfast is served!

09:15.876 --> 09:17.542
- Whoa! Is all this
- just for us,

09:17.584 --> 09:18.668
Or did Kate Middleton

09:18.669 --> 09:19.751
finally accept my

09:17.584 --> 09:19.751
brunch invitation?

09:20.834 --> 09:22.231
A syrup fountain

09:22.232 --> 09:23.626
for the pancakes?

09:23.667 --> 09:25.626
- Finally, somebody
- gets me!

09:27.083 --> 09:28.480
Ooh! Is that

09:28.481 --> 09:29.876
Rat a l'Orange?

09:27.083 --> 09:29.876
(CROAKING)

09:29.918 --> 09:31.147
Remember, Mrs. Kipling,

09:31.148 --> 09:32.375
pinky-claw up.

09:32.417 --> 09:33.959
(CROAKING)

09:35.000 --> 09:36.042
- Jessie?
- Yeah?

09:36.083 --> 09:37.542
- I hear you're
- taking German.

09:37.584 --> 09:38.668
I'd be happy to help you

09:38.669 --> 09:39.751
study for your test later.

09:39.792 --> 09:41.168
Oh, thanks but

09:41.169 --> 09:42.542
I'm just taking

09:39.792 --> 09:42.542
this class pass-fail.

09:42.584 --> 09:44.476
- You know, - less studying,
- More time with the kids.

09:44.500 --> 09:46.000
- I insist you
- let me tutor you.

09:46.042 --> 09:47.335
After all, one does want

09:47.336 --> 09:48.626
to do one's best.

09:48.667 --> 09:50.542
- Just say "yes" so he
- can keep cookin'.

09:50.584 --> 09:52.059
- (IN BRITISH ACCENT) - One does want
- More pancakes.

09:52.083 --> 09:53.417
(ALL CHUCKLE)

09:53.459 --> 09:55.042
- Yeah, less chatter,
- more batter.

09:55.083 --> 09:56.083
(ALL CHUCKLE)

09:57.918 --> 10:00.000
Hey, guys, so, uh...

10:00.042 --> 10:01.709
I made a big mis...

10:03.083 --> 10:04.584
Who's the dandy?

10:05.792 --> 10:07.042
Bertram, meet Roger.

10:07.083 --> 10:08.584
He's our new butler.

10:08.626 --> 10:09.813
He makes perfect pancakes.

10:09.814 --> 10:11.000
(JESSIE CHUCKLES)

10:11.042 --> 10:12.813
Sure, but can he make smiley

10:12.814 --> 10:14.584
faces out of chocolate chips,

10:11.042 --> 10:14.584
like I can?

10:14.626 --> 10:15.667
Better!

10:15.709 --> 10:16.731
Say hello

10:16.732 --> 10:17.751
to the Mona Lisa!

10:17.792 --> 10:19.000
(ALL CLAPPING)

10:20.876 --> 10:22.752
Yeah, I'd show you

10:22.753 --> 10:24.626
blueberry Derek Jeter, but...

10:24.667 --> 10:26.084
I ate him.

10:26.085 --> 10:27.500
(CHUCKLES)

10:27.542 --> 10:29.001
Um, Bertram,

10:29.002 --> 10:30.459
would you like to have

10:27.542 --> 10:30.459
breakfast with us?

10:31.083 --> 10:32.918
No, thank you.

10:32.959 --> 10:34.418
It seems like

10:34.419 --> 10:35.876
you're all getting along

10:32.959 --> 10:35.876
just fine without me.

10:35.918 --> 10:36.959
I, um, only came

10:36.960 --> 10:38.000
back to...

10:38.834 --> 10:40.375
Uh...

10:40.417 --> 10:42.083
Grab my spatula cozies.

10:42.125 --> 10:43.855
Personally, I like to let

10:43.856 --> 10:45.584
my utensils air dry.

10:45.626 --> 10:47.500
(GASPS) Air dry?

10:47.542 --> 10:48.751
Are you an animal?

10:50.667 --> 10:52.375
Well...

10:52.417 --> 10:54.042
I hope you and your

10:54.043 --> 10:55.667
water spots will all be

10:52.417 --> 10:55.667
very happy together!

10:57.876 --> 10:58.876
(DOOR CLOSING)

10:59.083 --> 11:00.792
Well...

11:00.834 --> 11:02.334
Someone's got his

11:02.335 --> 11:03.834
tea towel in a twist!

11:03.876 --> 11:05.688
Who's ready for the

11:05.689 --> 11:07.500
Eiffel Tower of bacon?

11:07.542 --> 11:08.876
(ALL GASPING)

11:08.918 --> 11:10.083
Wow!

11:10.125 --> 11:11.439
He combined my

11:11.440 --> 11:12.751
two favorite things.

11:12.792 --> 11:14.189
Nineteenth century

11:14.190 --> 11:15.584
French architecture and pork!

11:22.751 --> 11:23.814
(TELEVISION PLAYING)

11:23.815 --> 11:24.876
(VACUUMING)

11:26.959 --> 11:28.501
Uh, Roger? Do you think

11:28.502 --> 11:30.042
you could keep it down?

11:30.083 --> 11:31.563
We're trying

11:31.564 --> 11:33.042
to watch a movie!

11:33.083 --> 11:34.792
I don't know how you

11:34.793 --> 11:36.500
can see anything through

11:33.083 --> 11:36.500
this fog of filth!

11:36.542 --> 11:38.105
Ugh! Come on, guys,

11:38.106 --> 11:39.667
let's go make a snack.

11:39.709 --> 11:40.731
No! You can't go

11:40.732 --> 11:41.751
in there!

11:41.792 --> 11:43.667
- I've already cleaned
- the kitchen today.

11:43.709 --> 11:45.585
I hope that rule

11:45.586 --> 11:47.459
does not apply

11:43.709 --> 11:47.459
to the bathrooms.

11:47.500 --> 11:49.059
- Hey, Roger, why don't
- you take a break?

11:49.083 --> 11:50.834
- Yeah, play
- a game with us.

11:50.876 --> 11:52.252
No play until

11:52.253 --> 11:53.626
work is done.

11:53.667 --> 11:55.334
Bertram always used

11:55.335 --> 11:57.000
to drop everything

11:53.667 --> 11:57.000
to play hide-and-seek.

11:57.042 --> 11:58.792
- Actually, now that
- I think about it,

11:58.834 --> 11:59.834
He may have just been

11:59.835 --> 12:00.835
hiding from us.

12:00.876 --> 12:02.042
(SQUEAKING AND BANGING)

12:02.083 --> 12:03.709
(JESSIE GROANING)

12:05.751 --> 12:07.500
Hey, Roger.

12:07.542 --> 12:08.935
- Can you put up - a sign when you
- Wax the floors?

12:08.959 --> 12:11.080
- I banked off the - island and slid
- Into the stove.

12:12.751 --> 12:13.772
You didn't leave

12:13.773 --> 12:14.792
any scuff marks,

12:12.751 --> 12:14.792
did you?

12:14.834 --> 12:16.334
No, but I might have

12:16.335 --> 12:17.834
left some blood and

12:14.834 --> 12:17.834
a piece of my elbow.

12:19.083 --> 12:20.959
- So, Jessie,
- did you have a chance

12:21.000 --> 12:22.022
To study the German

12:22.023 --> 12:23.042
textbooks I left

12:21.000 --> 12:23.042
on your desk?

12:23.083 --> 12:24.355
Uh, yeah. Thanks.

12:24.356 --> 12:25.626
I scanned them.

12:25.667 --> 12:27.125
Scanning isn't studying.

12:27.167 --> 12:28.605
Scanning is for

12:28.606 --> 12:30.042
photocopiers and

12:27.167 --> 12:30.042
lazy students.

12:30.083 --> 12:31.563
I... Look Roger, I don't

12:31.564 --> 12:33.042
really need to speak

12:30.083 --> 12:33.042
perfect German.

12:33.083 --> 12:35.042
- Remember, this test
- is just pass-fail.

12:35.083 --> 12:37.059
- But you're setting - an example for
- These children.

12:37.083 --> 12:38.563
Do you want them

12:38.564 --> 12:40.042
to just pass-fail at life?

12:40.083 --> 12:41.584
Or excel?

12:41.626 --> 12:42.773
BOTH: Pass-fail!

12:42.774 --> 12:43.918
Excel!

12:46.751 --> 12:47.751
Excel!

12:48.292 --> 12:49.751
Of course you do.

12:49.792 --> 12:51.250
Now, trot on upstairs

12:51.292 --> 12:52.668
and don't come down

12:52.669 --> 12:54.042
until you know

12:51.292 --> 12:54.042
all the irregular verbs.

12:54.083 --> 12:55.500
You're an irregular verb!

12:56.209 --> 12:57.918
Pardon me?

12:57.959 --> 12:59.584
- I said,
- "Sorry to disturb."

13:01.083 --> 13:02.918
